[
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "3.2.2 Variances of U-statistics ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            123,
            97,
            539,
            117
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If $E [ h ( X _ { 1 } , . . . , X _ { m } ) ] ^ { 2 } < \\infty$ , then the variance of $U _ { n }$ in (3.11) with kernel $h$ has an explicit form. To derive ${ \\mathrm { V a r } } ( U _ { n } )$ , we need some notation. For $k = 1 , . . . , m$ , let ",
        "bbox": [
            123,
            130,
            872,
            186
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n\\begin{array}{l} h _ {k} \\left(x _ {1}, \\dots , x _ {k}\\right) = E \\left[ h \\left(X _ {1}, \\dots , X _ {m}\\right) \\mid X _ {1} = x _ {1}, \\dots , X _ {k} = x _ {k} \\right] \\\\ = E [ h (x _ {1}, \\dots , x _ {k}, X _ {k + 1}, \\dots , X _ {m}) ]. \\\\ \\end{array}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            225,
            196,
            769,
            241
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Note that $h _ { m } = h$ . It can be shown that ",
        "bbox": [
            123,
            253,
            535,
            270
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nh _ {k} \\left(x _ {1}, \\dots , x _ {k}\\right) = E \\left[ h _ {k + 1} \\left(x _ {1}, \\dots , x _ {k}, X _ {k + 1}\\right) \\right]. \\tag {3.14}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            289,
            283,
            867,
            304
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Define ",
        "bbox": [
            125,
            315,
            195,
            331
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n\\tilde {h} _ {k} = h _ {k} - E [ h \\left(X _ {1}, \\dots , X _ {m}\\right) ], \\tag {3.15}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            353,
            331,
            867,
            352
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$k = 1 , . . . , m$ , and $\\ddot { h } = \\ddot { h } _ { m }$ . Then, for any $U _ { n }$ defined by (3.11), ",
        "bbox": [
            123,
            357,
            744,
            378
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nU _ {n} - E \\left(U _ {n}\\right) = \\binom {n} {m} ^ {- 1} \\sum_ {c} \\tilde {h} \\left(X _ {i _ {1}}, \\dots , X _ {i _ {m}}\\right). \\tag {3.16}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            282,
            388,
            867,
            435
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Theorem 3.4 (Hoeffding’s theorem). For a U-statistic $U _ { n }$ given by (3.11) with $E [ h ( X _ { 1 } , . . . , X _ { m } ) ] ^ { 2 } < \\infty$ , ",
        "bbox": [
            123,
            463,
            867,
            501
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n\\operatorname {V a r} (U _ {n}) = \\binom {n} {m} ^ {- 1} \\sum_ {k = 1} ^ {m} \\binom {m} {k} \\binom {n - m} {m - k} \\zeta_ {k},\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            291,
            512,
            703,
            561
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where ",
        "bbox": [
            125,
            570,
            191,
            585
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n\\zeta_ {k} = \\operatorname {V a r} \\left(h _ {k} \\left(X _ {1}, \\dots , X _ {k}\\right)\\right).\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            366,
            588,
            624,
            608
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Proof. Consider two sets $\\{ i _ { 1 } , . . . , i _ { m } \\}$ and $\\{ j _ { 1 } , . . . , j _ { m } \\}$ of $m$ distinct integers from $\\{ 1 , . . . , n \\}$ with exactly $k$ integers in common. The number of distinct choices of two such sets is $\\binom { n } { m } \\left( { m \\atop k } \\right) \\left( { n { - } m \\atop m { - } k } \\right)$ . By the symmetry of $\\ddot { h } _ { m }$ and independence of $X _ { 1 } , . . . , X _ { n }$ , ",
        "bbox": [
            123,
            614,
            872,
            686
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\nE \\left[ \\tilde {h} \\left(X _ {i _ {1}}, \\dots , X _ {i _ {m}}\\right) \\tilde {h} \\left(X _ {j _ {1}}, \\dots , X _ {j _ {m}}\\right) \\right] = \\zeta_ {k} \\tag {3.17}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            305,
            696,
            867,
            720
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "for $k = 1 , . . . , m$ (exercise). Then, by (3.16), ",
        "bbox": [
            123,
            729,
            558,
            749
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "$$\n\\begin{array}{l} \\operatorname {V a r} (U _ {n}) = \\binom {n} {m} ^ {- 2} \\sum_ {c} \\sum_ {c} E [ \\tilde {h} (X _ {i _ {1}}, \\dots , X _ {i _ {m}}) \\tilde {h} (X _ {j _ {1}}, \\dots , X _ {j _ {m}}) ] \\\\ = \\binom {n} {m} ^ {- 2} \\sum_ {k = 1} ^ {m} \\binom {n} {m} \\binom {m} {k} \\binom {n - m} {m - k} \\zeta_ {k}. \\\\ \\end{array}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            195,
            759,
            794,
            857
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This proves the result. ",
        "bbox": [
            125,
            869,
            355,
            885
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
